events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — The Knicks are a young team that's still learning how to string together victories.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 37, Knicks rally to beat Celtics 120-117 in OT

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 25 points and the Detroit Pistons won in Brooklyn for the first time in nearly five years, beating the Nets 130-122 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons beat Nets, first win in Brooklyn in almost 5 years

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 28 points, Mason Plumlee added yet another strong performance with 21 points and 12 rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Chicago Bulls 111-96 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Plumlee lead Hornets past Bulls 111-96

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 26 points and Evan Mobley added 21 as the Cleveland Cavaliers routed the short-handed Houston Rockets 113-95 Thursday night despite missing Donovan Mitchell.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 26 as Cavaliers race past Rockets 113-95

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic's early injury on Thursday night gave the Dallas Mavericks a very valid reason to lose on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie scores 36, Mavs top Suns 99-95 after Doncic hurt

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — If anyone needed any proof of how confident Paul George and the Los Angeles Clippers are feeling, it came late in the second quarter of their game against the San Antonio Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers extend win streak to 4 with 138-100 rout of Spurs
